You are working in the Hackademic Solutions learning-object repository.

Before creating or reviewing content, use the durable context in:

- context/project-overview.md
- context/business-strategy.md
- context/brand-voice.md
- context/instructional-framework.md
- context/standards-strategy.md
- context/source-documents.md

Create structured, componentized learning-object folders directly in this workspace.

Do not print file contents to chat when asked to create files. Create or edit the actual files.

For each repo-ready learning object, create:

learning-objects/[category]/[slug]/
  index.md
  object.json
  components/
    anticipation-prompt.md
    read-core-concepts.md
    watch-scenario.md
    do-activity.md
    quiz.md
    reflection-prompt.md
    reuse-notes.md
    suggested-next-objects.md
  renders/
    skool.md
    linkedin.md
    slides.md
  metadata/
    scorm.json
    xapi-template.json
    review-checklist.md

Use lowercase kebab-case slugs and filenames.

The canonical source is the full learning-object folder.

index.md is the human-readable object map.

object.json is the machine-readable full object record.

The YAML front matter in index.md and the metadata in object.json must stay synchronized.

The component files contain the reusable instructional substance.

Renders and metadata are derived or support artifacts.

Use Read-Watch-Do.

Include an anticipation prompt before instruction.

Include a quiz component.

Include a reflection prompt after instruction.

Prepare SCORM 1.2 metadata, but do not claim full SCORM packaging exists.

Prepare xAPI-ready statement templates, but do not claim live xAPI tracking exists.

Create slide renders by default.

Use Hackademic Solutions voice: practical, academically grounded, clear, skeptical, useful, operationally fluent.

For deeper Microsoft, framework, governance, cybersecurity, AI security, legal, compliance, or standards-related subjects, require source references or flag source verification needed.

Flag unsupported claims, weak learning objectives, shallow DO activities, weak quiz items, weak SCORM metadata, weak xAPI evidence, and source verification gaps.

Favor reusable learning objects over one-off lessons.

Favor practical artifacts over passive content consumption.

If the user asks for a monolithic file, comply. Otherwise, prefer the componentized folder structure for repository-ready learning objects.
